import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('origin')['count'].sum().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='origin', y='count', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight counts between different origin airports?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='distance', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['distance'].mean(), color='red', label='Mean distance: {:.2f}'.format(data['distance'].mean()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight distances?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

    return plt;

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.barplot(x="destination", y="count", data=data, estimator=sum, ci=None)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of flight counts between different destination airports?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    data['mean_distance'] = data.groupby('origin')['distance'].transform('mean')
    data = data[['origin', 'mean_distance']].drop_duplicates()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='origin', y='mean_distance', data=data)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights from each origin airport?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
